WordNet::BestStem

Get the single best guess of word's stem form using text corpus frequencies of word forms.

DEPENDENCIES

WordNet  ( http://wordnet.princeton.edu )
WordNet::QueryData
WordNet::Similarity::ICFinder

INSTALLATION

Extract the files from the archive by entering this at a shell,

    tar xvf WordNet-BestStem-xxx.tar.gz

then,

    cd WordNet-BestStem-xxx

and run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    sudo make install

If you don't have permission to run sudo, you can specify an alternative path,

    perl Makefile.PL PREFIX=/home/user/my_perl_lib
    make
    make test
    make install

then add /home/user/my_perl_lib to your PERL5LIB environment variable.


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for the modules with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc WordNet::BestStem

You can also look for information at:

    Search CPAN
      http://search.cpan.org/dist/WordNet-BestStem/

If you notice a bug or have a request, or if you would like to help develop or maintain the package, please email me at the address below.


